00:15:03.750 --> 00:15:07.665
whereas the info you can edit
once before when you're paused

00:15:07.665 --> 00:15:08.750
or something like that.

00:15:08.750 --> 00:15:10.210
ROMAN NURIK: Yeah, and we'll
see on the phone, you still

00:15:10.210 --> 00:15:11.860
have access to this stuff.

00:15:11.860 --> 00:15:12.900
But it's just one swipe away.

00:15:12.900 --> 00:15:15.260
ADAM KOCH: It's just taking
advantage of the extra screen

00:15:15.260 --> 00:15:16.540
on the larger device.

00:15:16.540 --> 00:15:18.250
ROMAN NURIK: And then here, just
some examples of how you

00:15:18.250 --> 00:15:20.230
can present clips and
live effects.

00:15:20.230 --> 00:15:24.270
Obviously, pressing the dot,
dot, dot should take you to a

00:15:24.270 --> 00:15:27.850
customization or more effects
screen or something like that.

00:15:27.850 --> 00:15:29.990
So let's move on.

00:15:29.990 --> 00:15:31.790
So here's what it'll look
like on a phone.

00:15:31.790 --> 00:15:34.905
Again, very similar, it's just
that the effects portion is

00:15:34.905 --> 00:15:36.930
taken into a separate tab.

00:15:36.930 --> 00:15:38.210
And you have basically
the same UI.

00:15:38.210 --> 00:15:40.410
It's somewhat responsive.

00:15:40.410 --> 00:15:44.460
You still have slight changes
in core navigation between

00:15:44.460 --> 00:15:45.420
tablet and phone.

00:15:45.420 --> 00:15:49.020
But the core app is still
very much the same.

00:15:49.020 --> 00:15:50.260
So this is the recording
state.

00:15:50.260 --> 00:15:53.180
And now, what does it look
like in the pause state?

00:15:53.180 --> 00:15:54.950
So in the pause state,
you no longer have

00:15:54.950 --> 00:15:55.720
the option to mute.

00:15:55.720 --> 00:15:57.410
Mute doesn't make sense.

00:15:57.410 --> 00:15:59.300
And the Resume button
has basically

00:15:59.300 --> 00:16:00.920
been given extra treatment.

00:16:00.920 --> 00:16:02.950
Another thing I wanted to call
out is the Action Bar.

00:16:02.950 --> 00:16:08.000
So if you're recording, the Up
button should probably just

00:16:08.000 --> 00:16:10.960
take you up to the management
screen, that white

00:16:10.960 --> 00:16:12.340
screen that we had.

00:16:12.340 --> 00:16:14.920
And then you should show the
notification probably, or a

00:16:14.920 --> 00:16:19.000
persistent Now Recording
bar at the bottom.

00:16:19.000 --> 00:16:22.620
But if you're paused, it's an
indication that either you're

00:16:22.620 --> 00:16:27.020
temporarily taking a break
or you're done.

00:16:27.020 --> 00:16:29.060
You're actually done with
this recording session.

00:16:29.060 --> 00:16:32.040
You'll record more later,
but you're done.

00:16:32.040 --> 00:16:33.800
And so what we do is, we
actually changed the Action

00:16:33.800 --> 00:16:39.460
Bar to go from showing the Up
button to or the Done button

00:16:39.460 --> 00:16:43.640
to further give you the sense
that, hey, I can press Done.

00:16:43.640 --> 00:16:45.280
And I can then from
there, publish.

00:16:48.260 --> 00:16:50.820
We also looked at this
Info section,

00:16:50.820 --> 00:16:53.910
so editing the details.

00:16:53.910 --> 00:16:55.790
If you swipe over, you can
edit the title, the

00:16:55.790 --> 00:16:56.600
description.

00:16:56.600 --> 00:16:59.560
And you do still have this
persistent bar at the top to

00:16:59.560 --> 00:17:01.340
indicate that something
is happening.

00:17:01.340 --> 00:17:03.520
So you always want to
indicate that mode.

00:17:03.520 --> 00:17:06.720
If you're in that thick, heavy
mode, like navigation or

00:17:06.720 --> 00:17:09.290
playing music or something, you
always want to make sure

00:17:09.290 --> 00:17:11.680
that there's something on screen
that indicates that.

00:17:11.680 --> 00:17:12.950
And if it's in the app,
it could be a

00:17:12.950 --> 00:17:14.390
persistent bar like this.

00:17:14.390 --> 00:17:17.140
If you're out of the app, then
it should be a notification.

00:17:17.140 --> 00:17:20.260
ADAM KOCH: And it's worth noting
as well that the Mute

00:17:20.260 --> 00:17:22.869
and Pause buttons down here
are also persistent across

00:17:22.869 --> 00:17:25.445
these tabs, because you see
it here in the Info.

00:17:25.445 --> 00:17:28.040
And we saw on the
Record as well.

00:17:28.040 --> 00:17:29.790
So that's that thick state
coming to the front again,

00:17:29.790 --> 00:17:31.090
being able to control
it from any of

00:17:31.090 --> 00:17:32.430
these different screens.

00:17:32.430 --> 00:17:34.070
And then, of course, if you exit
out of the app, you've

00:17:34.070 --> 00:17:36.060
got the notification there
to control it.

00:17:36.060 --> 00:17:37.520
ROMAN NURIK: Yeah, and if you
swipe over to Effects--

00:17:37.520 --> 00:17:40.170
and this is one of the biggest
reasons for this--

00:17:40.170 --> 00:17:42.160
if you're in Effects, if you're
playing an intro clip,

00:17:42.160 --> 00:17:44.250
you probably want to mute
yourself for a moment.

00:17:44.250 --> 00:17:46.320
So you press Mute, press
the intro clip.

00:17:46.320 --> 00:17:48.140
And soon as that's done
playing, you unmute.

00:17:48.140 --> 00:17:51.310
So it's very easy from a single
screen at any point to

00:17:51.310 --> 00:17:52.560
do what you want to do.

00:17:54.780 --> 00:17:57.400
I think one of the last
components of this is, what

00:17:57.400 --> 00:18:01.200
happens when you're in the Info
screen and you're paused?

00:18:01.200 --> 00:18:03.340
At that point, you probably
want to give the user the

00:18:03.340 --> 00:18:04.860
option to preview and publish.

00:18:04.860 --> 00:18:06.890
If they press Preview and
Publish, it takes them to

00:18:06.890 --> 00:18:09.420
separate flow, where
they can maybe even

00:18:09.420 --> 00:18:11.640
edit, maybe make tweaks.

00:18:11.640 --> 00:18:15.780
But they can preview what
they've currently recorded.

00:18:15.780 --> 00:18:19.660
Once they're ready, it'll
upload using a ongoing

00:18:19.660 --> 00:18:22.960
notification with an upload
progress, and then publish

00:18:22.960 --> 00:18:24.990
when they're ready.

00:18:24.990 --> 00:18:27.680
So pretty straightforward,
a lot of this stuff is.

00:18:27.680 --> 00:18:29.370
There's nothing very
revolutionary.

00:18:29.370 --> 00:18:31.270
But here, you just want to
approach a creation a podcast

00:18:31.270 --> 00:18:32.570
creation app.

00:18:32.570 --> 00:18:35.790
I think there's one more
screen on editing.

00:18:35.790 --> 00:18:39.570
So we didn't spend the time to
figure out where this would go

00:18:39.570 --> 00:18:42.430
into the greater scheme
of the app.

00:18:42.430 --> 00:18:46.200
But one of the things that's
interesting is, this is a

00:18:46.200 --> 00:18:51.630
different type of medium that
you're probably used to.

00:18:51.630 --> 00:18:54.420
On Android, you're probably
used to editing photos or

00:18:54.420 --> 00:18:56.070
editing text or selecting
text.

00:18:56.070 --> 00:19:01.240
But you could use the same
metaphors and the same visuals

00:19:01.240 --> 00:19:02.830
to apply to audio.

00:19:02.830 --> 00:19:06.340
So you can do something like
long press on the audio to

00:19:06.340 --> 00:19:09.080
select a second or so, and then
show those little drag

00:19:09.080 --> 00:19:11.950
candles so that you can
drag them around.

00:19:11.950 --> 00:19:13.420
And then you can have
an insertion point.

00:19:13.420 --> 00:19:16.430
So if you have something
in the clipboard, then

00:19:16.430 --> 00:19:18.610
you can do a paste.

00:19:18.610 --> 00:19:19.790
You should also offer things--

00:19:19.790 --> 00:19:23.050
we didn't show this here-- but
things like, fade out, fade

00:19:23.050 --> 00:19:24.630
in, all sorts of effects.

00:19:24.630 --> 00:19:28.050
Those are very contextual to the
current point in the audio

00:19:28.050 --> 00:19:28.940
you're looking at.

00:19:28.940 --> 00:19:33.050
So definitely make sure to use
this type of UI if you're

00:19:33.050 --> 00:19:34.550
doing editing.

00:19:34.550 --> 00:19:35.690
I think it would make
a lot of sense.

00:19:35.690 --> 00:19:37.760
ADAM KOCH: And we were chatting
about a pretty neat

