00:20:39.300 --> 00:20:41.680
by a very talented developer.

00:20:41.680 --> 00:20:42.920
ROMAN NURIK: So with that,
I think that was

00:20:42.920 --> 00:20:44.050
it for podcast creation.

00:20:44.050 --> 00:20:45.860
I think we're about halfway.

00:20:45.860 --> 00:20:50.140
So let's move on to
design tools.

00:20:50.140 --> 00:20:51.580
So design tools--

00:20:51.580 --> 00:20:57.020
when we talk about design tools,
we like to break things

00:20:57.020 --> 00:21:00.680
out by the hat you wear,
the discipline.

00:21:00.680 --> 00:21:03.430
So we don't just talk about,
here's the basic design tool

00:21:03.430 --> 00:21:04.830
for designers.

00:21:04.830 --> 00:21:06.165
There's different disciplines--
interaction

00:21:06.165 --> 00:21:10.010
design, visual design, motion
design, asset production,

00:21:10.010 --> 00:21:12.830
which is a very specific thing
to Android, creating

00:21:12.830 --> 00:21:14.360
nine-patches and things
like that.

00:21:14.360 --> 00:21:18.800
So we like to break down the
tools that you should be using

00:21:18.800 --> 00:21:23.750
based on these hats
that people wear.

00:21:23.750 --> 00:21:25.680
And you'll see a little circle
in each of these slides

00:21:25.680 --> 00:21:28.960
indicating who this is for.

00:21:28.960 --> 00:21:31.390
So the very first set of tools--
and this is very, very

00:21:31.390 --> 00:21:33.540
obvious-- but the Adobe
Creative Suite.

00:21:33.540 --> 00:21:35.250
And this is Illustrator,

00:21:35.250 --> 00:21:37.450
Fireworks, Photoshop, InDesign.

00:21:37.450 --> 00:21:40.800
Three things that I really
want to quickly call out.

00:21:40.800 --> 00:21:44.110
The first is that we do have
official Android stencils

00:21:44.110 --> 00:21:45.330
available for these.

00:21:45.330 --> 00:21:50.490
And so what you saw today with
the podcast creation app was

00:21:50.490 --> 00:21:55.040
using the official Android
stencils for Illustrator.

00:21:55.040 --> 00:21:57.240
The next is that, most of the
Android design team, as far as

00:21:57.240 --> 00:22:02.070
I know, they use Illustrator,
Fireworks, and Photoshop.

00:22:02.070 --> 00:22:03.640
Illustrator is very,
very common with

00:22:03.640 --> 00:22:05.085
our interaction designers.

00:22:05.085 --> 00:22:07.450
For visual design, I think
mostly they use

00:22:07.450 --> 00:22:09.220
Photoshop and Fireworks.

00:22:09.220 --> 00:22:11.490
But Fireworks can actually
work really well for

00:22:11.490 --> 00:22:14.310
interaction design as well,
because it can actually create

00:22:14.310 --> 00:22:17.880
clickable sections, like you can
have interactive mockups.

00:22:17.880 --> 00:22:19.910
I think I demoed this
two years ago.

00:22:19.910 --> 00:22:22.660
You can create an interactive
PDF where you click on

00:22:22.660 --> 00:22:24.810
different things, and it takes
you to different pages.

00:22:24.810 --> 00:22:29.870
It's a much nicer way to
visualize a flow or to

00:22:29.870 --> 00:22:31.410
visualize a sequence of
events in your app.

00:22:31.410 --> 00:22:34.150
So definitely consider
doing that.

00:22:34.150 --> 00:22:37.260
And there's a recent article on
smashingmag.com on how to

00:22:37.260 --> 00:22:39.700
use InDesign to do something
very similar.

00:22:39.700 --> 00:22:41.370
I haven't tried this myself,
but it seems really

00:22:41.370 --> 00:22:41.830
interesting.

00:22:41.830 --> 00:22:43.980
So if you're doing interaction
design, definitely check out

00:22:43.980 --> 00:22:46.140
this article about InDesign
interaction design.

00:22:49.390 --> 00:22:53.760
Let's move on to some other
interaction design tools.

00:22:53.760 --> 00:22:55.750
For interaction design,
obviously, one of the things

00:22:55.750 --> 00:22:58.750
you want to is sketch a lot--
a lot, a lot, a lot.

00:22:58.750 --> 00:23:03.390
But there are also some software
tools for sketching

00:23:03.390 --> 00:23:04.940
for creating wire frames
and especially

00:23:04.940 --> 00:23:06.150
interactive wire frames.

00:23:06.150 --> 00:23:08.020
Here's a quick selection
of them.

00:23:08.020 --> 00:23:11.890
I generally prefer using
OmniGraffle, since we have

00:23:11.890 --> 00:23:13.870
officials stencils for those.

00:23:13.870 --> 00:23:17.700
And you could actually do both
low and high fidelity wire

00:23:17.700 --> 00:23:18.510
frames there.

00:23:18.510 --> 00:23:20.140
Almost all the other tools,
since they don't have the

00:23:20.140 --> 00:23:23.590
official stencils, they have
unofficial stencils, which

00:23:23.590 --> 00:23:26.480
aren't really high fidelity,
which is fine, for wire frames

00:23:26.480 --> 00:23:28.750
it's totally OK.

00:23:28.750 --> 00:23:32.180
And actually, the last three
here-- fluid UI, Proto.io and

00:23:32.180 --> 00:23:33.230
Balsamiq Mockups--

00:23:33.230 --> 00:23:35.380
those are also really good,
because they're web based.

00:23:35.380 --> 00:23:38.650
And what that means is that
you can create actual

00:23:38.650 --> 00:23:43.650
prototypes, deploy them to a
website, and share them with

00:23:43.650 --> 00:23:45.940
your product manager.

00:23:45.940 --> 00:23:49.940
I think you can create logins
for other design team members,

00:23:49.940 --> 00:23:51.970
so you can have multiple members
of the design team

00:23:51.970 --> 00:23:54.770
working on the same project
all along the web.

00:23:54.770 --> 00:23:56.320
So some pretty cool
stuff there.

00:23:56.320 --> 00:23:59.230
And then Proto.io was actually
something that Paul Burke

00:23:59.230 --> 00:24:02.630
recently mentioned to us,
basically something that lets

00:24:02.630 --> 00:24:05.760
you actually mock up gestures
as well as you can do, like

00:24:05.760 --> 00:24:08.590
scrolling and swiping and
things like that.

00:24:08.590 --> 00:24:09.740
So lots of good tools here.

00:24:09.740 --> 00:24:12.460
And there's more than just
these, obviously, but here's

00:24:12.460 --> 00:24:15.530
the quick selection
of some of them.

00:24:15.530 --> 00:24:19.420
Here's what Fluid UI looks like,
just a quick example of

00:24:19.420 --> 00:24:22.870
the interactive mockup
so you can create.

00:24:22.870 --> 00:24:27.000
So in this case, this My Agenda
tab, when you click

00:24:27.000 --> 00:24:31.150
that in the final interactive
HTML file, it actually takes

00:24:31.150 --> 00:24:33.780
you to a different page, so you
can create these links.

00:24:33.780 --> 00:24:35.030
It's really cool.

00:24:37.870 --> 00:24:39.020
The next thing we wanted
to talk about was

00:24:39.020 --> 00:24:40.240
Android Design Preview.

00:24:40.240 --> 00:24:43.580
So this is more for
visual designers.

00:24:43.580 --> 00:24:48.000
And this basically lets you
mirror a portion of your

00:24:48.000 --> 00:24:52.530
screen from your computer
to your Android device.

00:24:52.530 --> 00:24:55.280
So let's say you have Photoshop
open, and you have a

00:24:55.280 --> 00:24:57.950
high fidelity visual
mockup open.

00:24:57.950 --> 00:25:02.460
This is actually something from
one of our past episodes.

00:25:02.460 --> 00:25:04.540
So all you need to do is, you
need to open up the Android

00:25:04.540 --> 00:25:05.670
Design Preview app.

00:25:05.670 --> 00:25:09.160
It's this little window
that pops up here.

00:25:09.160 --> 00:25:11.860
You can then drag around
this red rectangle.

00:25:11.860 --> 00:25:12.180
It's kind of faint.

00:25:12.180 --> 00:25:13.200
You can't really see it.

00:25:13.200 --> 00:25:16.980
But you drag it to encapsulate
your part of the screen that

00:25:16.980 --> 00:25:21.040
you want to mirror And then it
mirrors that to your device.

00:25:21.040 --> 00:25:25.130
What's not pictured here is the
USB cable that you need

00:25:25.130 --> 00:25:25.920
plugged in.

00:25:25.920 --> 00:25:30.470
So you do need to use USB, and
it doesn't work over Wi-Fi

00:25:30.470 --> 00:25:32.590
currently, but it's definitely
a good tool to

00:25:32.590 --> 00:25:33.998
have in your arsenal.

00:25:37.390 --> 00:25:39.410
Next, we have--

00:25:39.410 --> 00:25:41.200
actually, I'm going to spend a
little bit of time on this.

00:25:41.200 --> 00:25:48.340
So a lot of designers on
Android, they often lament

00:25:48.340 --> 00:25:51.320
that there's a lot of asset
production work to do.

00:25:51.320 --> 00:25:53.210
And you have to create
nine-patches.

00:25:53.210 --> 00:25:55.770
And you have to create all these
different states for

00:25:55.770 --> 00:25:58.850
buttons and things and
tabs and whatnot.

00:25:58.850 --> 00:26:01.010
And certainly, there
are a lot of things

00:26:01.010 --> 00:26:02.130
you do need to create.

00:26:02.130 --> 00:26:04.900
To create a really awesome app,
you need to think about

00:26:04.900 --> 00:26:09.520
different screen densities
and things like that.

00:26:09.520 --> 00:26:11.000
But there are a lot of
tools out there that

00:26:11.000 --> 00:26:12.460
can help in the process.

00:26:12.460 --> 00:26:14.690
And this is especially true if
you're following the Holo

00:26:14.690 --> 00:26:15.650
visual language.

00:26:15.650 --> 00:26:18.180
So if you have your completely
custom UI, there's not really

00:26:18.180 --> 00:26:20.170
anything that'll help
you with that.

00:26:20.170 --> 00:26:22.780
There are some tools, like some
Photoshop actions and

00:26:22.780 --> 00:26:26.580
Fireworks plug-ins that
will do that.

00:26:26.580 --> 00:26:29.200
But for the most part, if you're
following Holo, there's

00:26:29.200 --> 00:26:31.530
some really good tools
online for this.

00:26:31.530 --> 00:26:33.360
So the first is the Android
Asset Studio.

00:26:33.360 --> 00:26:35.830
We covered this before, so I
won't go into detail on it.

00:26:35.830 --> 00:26:38.760
But the next is the Actual Bar
Style Generator, which we

00:26:38.760 --> 00:26:40.050
talked about in a
past episode.

00:26:40.050 --> 00:26:41.960
I just want to reiterate
how important it

00:26:41.960 --> 00:26:43.780
is to use this tool.

00:26:43.780 --> 00:26:48.350
Basically, it lets you very
quickly throw in a few colors.

00:26:48.350 --> 00:26:51.980
And it would generate all this
stuff, all the cruft, the XML

00:26:51.980 --> 00:26:54.900
files, the PNG files, basically
everything that you

00:26:54.900 --> 00:26:58.720
need to get your Action Bar
to base level of theming.

00:26:58.720 --> 00:27:00.000
ADAM KOCH: It's a
good jump start.

00:27:00.000 --> 00:27:02.370
And I think it's also compatible
with the Action Bar

00:27:02.370 --> 00:27:02.830
Sherlock as well.

00:27:02.830 --> 00:27:03.240
ROMAN NURIK: Yeah,
that's right.

00:27:03.240 --> 00:27:06.870
So there's an option to create
Sherlock styles.

00:27:06.870 --> 00:27:08.360
So if you're using Action
Bar Sherlock, it'll

00:27:08.360 --> 00:27:10.830
just work with you.

00:27:10.830 --> 00:27:14.480
And I just can't stress how
important it is to use this in

00:27:14.480 --> 00:27:17.550
addition to Action Bar Sherlock,
in addition to the

00:27:17.550 --> 00:27:19.910
core Action Bar APIs
rather than try to

00:27:19.910 --> 00:27:21.010
build your own thing.

00:27:21.010 --> 00:27:24.810
If you try to build your own
custom Action Bar, you're

00:27:24.810 --> 00:27:26.350
going to have to re implement
a lot of stuff.

00:27:26.350 --> 00:27:28.030
And it's just not going
to look as good.

00:27:28.030 --> 00:27:32.260
So definitely use this
tool if you can.

00:27:32.260 --> 00:27:35.465
And the last tool, which is, I
think, even more impressive in

00:27:35.465 --> 00:27:36.800
its technical--

00:27:36.800 --> 00:27:39.520
and the amount of stuff
it does for you is

00:27:39.520 --> 00:27:41.700
Android Holo Colors.

00:27:41.700 --> 00:27:46.650
So Android Holo Colors is very
similar to Action Bar, to the

00:27:46.650 --> 00:27:49.120
Action Bar Style Generator,
except it creates UI

00:27:49.120 --> 00:27:49.810
controls for you.

00:27:49.810 --> 00:27:52.650
So if you want purple--

00:27:52.650 --> 00:27:56.340
let's say your core brand
accent is purple--

00:27:56.340 --> 00:27:58.770
if you want purple check boxes
and purple buttons and purple

00:27:58.770 --> 00:28:01.620
text fields and everything,
Android Holo Colors will

00:28:01.620 --> 00:28:02.980
generate all this for you.

00:28:02.980 --> 00:28:06.500
You basically tell it which UI
controllers you want to create

00:28:06.500 --> 00:28:08.650
or which controllers you plan on
using, and it will generate

00:28:08.650 --> 00:28:10.680
those assets for you.

00:28:10.680 --> 00:28:12.990
The last thing I wanted to
mention is, with the Action

00:28:12.990 --> 00:28:15.510
Bar Style Generator, it's not
only good for creating Action

00:28:15.510 --> 00:28:18.460
Bar assets, it's also good for
creating touch states.

00:28:18.460 --> 00:28:21.680
So the standard touch state
on Android is this

00:28:21.680 --> 00:28:24.400
semi-transparent blue overlay.

00:28:24.400 --> 00:28:27.580
But let's say your brand
accent is not blue.

00:28:27.580 --> 00:28:31.170
Let's say you want to actually
use something like red or

00:28:31.170 --> 00:28:33.170
purple or whatever.

00:28:33.170 --> 00:28:35.050
One of the things that the
Action Bar Style Generator

00:28:35.050 --> 00:28:38.620
does is, it creates a stateless
drawable, which is

00:28:38.620 --> 00:28:45.900
kind of a stateful graphic that
contains the assets for

00:28:45.900 --> 00:28:47.110
the different states.

00:28:47.110 --> 00:28:49.990
So if there's nothing, it's
just transparent.

00:28:49.990 --> 00:28:53.100
If it's pressed, it will
actually use your accent color

00:28:53.100 --> 00:28:54.360
as that overlay.

00:28:54.360 --> 00:28:59.030
And if it's focused, meaning the
user has selected the item

00:28:59.030 --> 00:29:03.760
with the keyboard, it'll use the
standard focus style with

00:29:03.760 --> 00:29:05.710
different levels of
translucency.

00:29:05.710 --> 00:29:07.600
But it'll still apply
your accent color.

00:29:07.600 --> 00:29:09.790
So the Action Bar Style
Generator is really good for

00:29:09.790 --> 00:29:11.430
generating that.

00:29:11.430 --> 00:29:14.050
And I'd say that the combination
of these two tools

00:29:14.050 --> 00:29:17.210
gets you most of the way for
baseline branding of an app.

00:29:17.210 --> 00:29:18.320
So definitely use them--

00:29:18.320 --> 00:29:21.660
really important to do that.

00:29:21.660 --> 00:29:25.000
Last thing for design tools--
and we'll probably talk more

00:29:25.000 --> 00:29:26.760
